00:46:15.060 --> 00:46:19.939
sophisticated events because it's a hundred percent stochastic. So in the insurance industry,

00:46:19.939 --> 00:46:28.500
it's all Bayesian type. You say our portfolio of losses is a log normal distribution with these

00:46:28.500 --> 00:46:33.860
parameters. Here is the fit that proves it out. And then you begin to do all sorts of

00:46:33.860 --> 00:46:39.060
